{"type":"text","timestamp":1778783267034,"sessionID":"ses_1d8461b99ffelloRWu4Z0us23q","part":{"id":"prt_e27be8e2b0011Vz0xJ3hoqIZVr","messageID":"msg_e27be78b10014Gzx8oxfubC9RB","sessionID":"ses_1d8461b99ffelloRWu4Z0us23q","type":"text","text":"Let me understand the task:\n\n**T1.1: Write adapter tests first**\n\nThis is about writing tests for the Waveplan adapter mapping. The task involves:\n- `internal/contextsize/adapter/waveplan.go` - the adapter (not yet created)\n- `internal/contextsize/adapter/waveplan_test.go` - the test file\n- `docs/plans/2026-05-13-cloudflare-ai-worker-execution-waves.json` - a sample execution waves file\n\nI need to:\n1. Read the spec and plan docs to understand what the adapter should do\n\n\n2. Look at the existing codebase structure\n3. Read the cloudflare execution waves file (fixture)\n4. Write tests FIRST (TDD)\n5. Then implement minimal code to pass\n\nLet me start by reading the spec and plan, and exploring the existing codebase.\n</think>\n\nUsing **fp-implement** to claim/work on FP-ADAPTER-MAP and **TDD** to write tests first.\n\nLet me load context from the spec, plan, and existing codebase.\n\n\n\n\n\n","time":{"start":1778783260203,"end":1778783267027}}}
