{"type":"text","timestamp":1778783290435,"sessionID":"ses_1d8461b99ffelloRWu4Z0us23q","part":{"id":"prt_e27beec95001x4arRoeuzFsQtz","messageID":"msg_e27bed30e001h9g6ulRS7TX35a","sessionID":"ses_1d8461b99ffelloRWu4Z0us23q","type":"text","text":"Now I have a clear picture. The adapter files already exist with implementation and tests. Let me check the current state:\n\n1. `waveplan.go` - Already has full implementation of `FromWaveplanTask` and `FromWaveplanUnit`\n2. `waveplan_test.go` - Already has tests covering:\n   - Task file/doc_ref resolution\n   - Unit doc_ref resolution\n   - Unknown task/unit ID errors\n   - Deduped/sorted referenced_files\n   - Task dependency collapse from unit edges\n   - Empty depends_on\n   - Unit depends_on\n   - Empty plan path errors\n   - Missing doc_ref errors\n   - Source is \"waveplan\"\n   - Structurally valid for estimator\n\nThe task T1.1 is \"Write adapter tests first\" - but the tests are already written. This is a resumed task, so I need to verify the tests pass and check if there's anything missing. Looking at the spec requirements, I'm checking what the task should cover: task-level conversion from execution-waves JSON, unit-level conversion, and doc_ref resolution.\n\nThe existing tests cover most of these areas, but I'm noticing the spec mentions rejecting invalid selector combinations like `--candidate` with `--plan` and `--task` with `--unit`. However, those validation rules belong in the CLI wrapper layer, not the adapter itself, so they shouldn't be in the adapter tests. Let me run the tests to see what's actually failing and determine what still needs to be done.\n</think>\n\nGood — the adapter files already exist from a prior session. Let me verify the tests pass and check for any gaps against the spec requirements.\n\n","time":{"start":1778783284373,"end":1778783290431}}}
